e an important source of information, both to Canadians and to interested groups around the world. The Encyclopedia of Canadian Social Work is available in e-book version by subscription or from university and college libraries through the following vendors: Canadian Electronic Library, Ebrary, MyiLibrary, and Netlibrary.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aSocial sciences. 0aSocial servicezCanadavEncyclopedias. 0aSocial servicezCanada. 0aSocial workerszCanadavEncyclopedias. 0aSocial workerszCanada. 4aSocial Science: Social Work. 7aREFERENCE / Encyclopedias.2bisacsh1 aTurner, Francis J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978088920915240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780889209152423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780889209152/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles